Definition: the dead body of a human being
Example: the cadaver was intended for dissection; the end of the police search was the discovery of a corpse; the murderer confessed that he threw the stiff in the river; honor comes to bless the turf that wraps their clay
Synonyms: adj, pert, cadaverous, cadaveric, corpse, stiff, noun, communication, slang, u, clay, remains, dead_body, the, dead, body, of, a, human, being, was, intended, for, dissection, end, police, search, discovery, murderer, confessed, that, he, threw, in, river, honor, comes, to, bless, turf, wraps, their
Category: noun.body
